Blockchain: Ethereum (Sepolia Testnet)
Smart Contracts: Solidity
Solidity is a contract-oriented language used to implement smart contracts â€” programs that automatically execute the terms of an agreement. It is statically typed, supports inheritance, libraries, complex user-defined types, and more.
Created by: Ethereum team (initially proposed by Gavin Wood)
